  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large kazan over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the minced garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 1 minute.",
    "Add the rice flour chapssalgaru and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the water and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cover the kazan with a lid.",
    "Cook for 15 minutes, or until the mixture is dry and the rice is cooked.",
    "Stir in the black pepper, salt, and sweet paprika.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a serving dish and top with chopped fresh parsley.",
    "If using, crumble the feta cheese and dollop the sour cream on top.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
